race.comment: The well-related YOYO YEEZY (10) (half to G1 winner Uncommon James) couldn't have been more impressive saluting over this track and trip before the spell and is drawn to get a cosy run in transit from gate two. Revved up for this with a recent trial victory and a strong showing while fresh would not surprise. BARBERRY SPUR (7) placed over this course and distance first-up and will have come on with that run now under the belt. Can improve enough to take this out. HEARTS ARE BETTER (2) may have suffered from the dreaded second-up syndrome last time out but go on the strong win here when resuming. Top-three aspirations on best form. MOULIN MISS (6) has gotten better with each run this campaign and that culminated with a solid Doomben win at the latest effort. Can go back-to-back. SCRIPTED (8) is yet to taste defeat in two career outings and shouldn't be discounted lightly.
